            <div class="recap-section">
                <div class="recap-title">üìñ Sessions 1 &amp; 2 Comprehensive Recap (20 minutes)</div>
                <div class="recap-content">
                    <strong>Session 1 Summary:</strong> We covered AI fundamentals, effective prompting techniques, and using AI for course development‚Äîincluding content creation, research, curriculum design, and discussion question generation. SGLs practiced basic technical skills like document uploads and browser management.
                    <br><br>
                    <strong>Session 2 Summary:</strong> We focused on course analysis and optimization, learning to analyze Zoom transcripts for engagement patterns, process student feedback, identify areas of confusion, and apply insights to improve teaching. SGLs practiced adaptive teaching strategies and created supplementary materials.
                    <br><br>
                    <strong>Interactive Recap:</strong> Each SGL briefly shares one key takeaway from Sessions 1 &amp; 2 and one implementation success or challenge. This sets the stage for peer learning throughout the workshop.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="session-section">
                <div class="section-title">Learning Objectives</div>
                <ul class="objectives-list">
                    <li>Troubleshoot real challenges encountered during implementation</li>
                    <li>Master advanced AI applications: visual aids creation, comparative analysis, immersive reading</li>
                    <li>Configure and optimize dual screen setups for efficient Zoom session management</li>
                    <li>Manage Zoom screen sharing effectively while presenting AI-generated visualizations</li>
                    <li>Navigate between multiple windows and applications during live Zoom sessions</li>
                    <li>Share specific application windows vs. entire screen for optimal presentation</li>
                    <li>Use Zoom whiteboard features to annotate AI-generated content in real-time</li>
                    <li>Manage participant engagement while switching between AI tools and presentation materials</li>
                    <li>Handle technical issues during Zoom sessions (audio/video, screen share problems, participant questions)</li>
                    <li>Plan for continuous improvement and experimentation beyond the course</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

