            <h2>üéØ Why This Structure Works</h2>
            <div class="info-grid">
                <div class="info-item">
                    <div class="info-label">Progressive Learning</div>
                    <div class="info-value">Build skills incrementally: foundation ‚Üí practice ‚Üí mastery. Each session builds on real implementation experience.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="info-item">
                    <div class="info-label">Active Teaching Integration</div>
                    <div class="info-value">SGLs practice between sessions during their actual courses, bringing real challenges and successes to discuss.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="info-item">
                    <div class="info-label">Timing Optimization</div>
                    <div class="info-value">Session 2 occurs mid-term when SGLs have transcripts to analyze. Session 3 in May allows for full-term reflection.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="info-item">
                    <div class="info-label">In-Person Value</div>
                    <div class="info-value">After building skills online, SGLs arrive with specific questions, documented experiences, and readiness for advanced learning.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="info-item">
                    <div class="info-label">Peer Learning</div>
                    <div class="info-value">Multiple opportunities for SGLs to learn from each other's diverse course types and teaching approaches.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="info-item">
                    <div class="info-label">Reduced Barrier to Entry</div>
                    <div class="info-value">Online start means broader participation without travel. In-person finale rewards committed participants.</div>
                </div>
            </div>
